news.title: Lucknow: Yazdan Apartment owners move HC seeking stay on demolition
news.para: Their lawyers requested the bench to take up the petition on Monday considering the urgency. The bench agreed but by the time the petition came up for hearing the court was short of time.

news.title: Nashik civic body collects Rs 50.4 crore under 1% local body tax in seven months
news.para: This is part of the total grant of Rs 50.45 crore that NMC has received in the first seven months (April-October) of the current financial year, which is 35% more than the grant the civic body received last financial year.

news.title: Kanpur development body invites applications for sale of plots from Nov 16
news.para: The KDA housing schemes where the plots are situated are Jarauli, Ispat Nagar, Kalpi Nagar, Vyapar Nagar, Vaidehi Nagar, Cattle Colony, Kidwai Nagar Block Y-1, Shujat Ganj Block- B, Swarn Jayanti Vihar, Mahaveer Nagar Extension and Shatabdi Nagar Sector-4.

news.title: No bail for directors of Hindustan Construction Company in Rs 50 crore tax case
news.para: Special public prosecutor Amit Munde had opposed a stay on the order. ​​The prosecution said that on the last date, the court had directed the accused to remain present before it on Monday.

news.title: Gurugram civic body fines 221 for violation of GRAP norms
news.para: The highest number of fines were issued for keeping construction material uncovered as 99 people were imposed penalties amounting to Rs 10.2 lakh.

news.title: Telangana government to raise Rs 2,000 crore through auction of open plots, flats
news.para: The state government has been doing massive auctions for open plots since February this year as part of resource mobilisation for the state government. The government earned about 5,000 crore in Hyderabad and other districts through auctions.

news.title: BSNL lists 13 properties on MSTC website for auction
news.para: The company has invited bids by December 5 for sale of 13 properties in Andhra Pradesh, Madhya Pradesh, Gujarat, Telangana and Uttar Pradesh, BSNL said in a statement.

news.title: Chintels India asks why government report silent on Bhayana Builders
news.para: In its report submitted on November 8, the four-member committee led by additional deputy commissioner Vishram Kumar Meena concluded that rapid and early corrosion of steel reinforcements due to the presence of excessive chloride in concrete was the root cause of the vertical collapse of living room floors at Tower D of the condominium.

news.title: Curbs imposed in Delhi-NCR under stage III of GRAP lifted
news.para: ​This means construction and demolition activities can resume in the region. However, user agencies need to strictly follow dust control norms.

news.title: Lenders vote for six projects of HDIL, four projects to be liquidated
news.para: Lenders voted in favour of Adani Properties for Project BKC and Shahad Maharal Lands, while Dev Land and Housing Pvt Ltd won HDIL Tower. Separately a consortium of Khyati Realtors and Dosti Realty Ltd won three projects- Majestic Towers, Whispering Towers and Premier Kurla.

news.title: Parsvnath Developers' net loss widens to Rs 99.40 crore in Q2 FY23
news.para: The company's net consolidated income stood at Rs 44.76 crore in Q2 FY23, a dip of 3.60 per cent from Rs 46.43 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Ashiana Housing posts net loss of Rs 1.61 crore in Q2 FY23
news.para: The company's net consolidated income stood at Rs 91.72 crore in Q2 FY23, a growth of of 13.67 per cent from Rs 80.69 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Shriram Properties posts net profit of Rs 19.59 crore in Q2 FY23
news.para: The company's net consolidated income stood at Rs 275.83 crore in Q2 FY23, a growth of 192.72 per cent from Rs 94.23 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: China allows property developers to access some pre-sale funds
news.para: The notice follows an extensive package outlined by Chinese regulators to shore up financing in the struggling property sector. Chinese property stocks and bonds surged on Monday as the market cheered the measures.

news.title: Keystone Realtors IPO subscribed 8% on Day 1
news.para: The Rs 635-crore IPO received bids for 7,24,599 shares against 86,47,858 shares on offer, according to an update available with the NSE.
